      <description>Part of a floor mosaic, located in the Corrider of the Great Hunt, at Villa
         Romana del Casale at Piazza Armerina. Depicted in the apse (top) is a dark-skinned female
         figure, surrounded by a phoenix, elephant and tiger. This figure may be an allegory for
         Arabia or India, representing the Eastern border of the world as known to the Romans. The
         rest of the mosaic depicts a hunt: visible in the center is a griffin, clawing at a box
         containing human bait.</description>
